definition.value: A tissue-specific cytoplasmic vesicle surrounded by a membrane half-leaflet within which carotenoid pigments are stored. Carotenoid vescicles are synthesized in xanthophores and erythrophore cells and are yellow, orange or red in appearance.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoisocaproate + CoA -eq- (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-oxoisocaproate + NADH + H+ -eq- (R)-2-hydroxyisocaproate + NAD+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  pyruvate + acetyl-CoA + H2O -eq- (R)-citramalate + CoA.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2,3-diketo-5-methylthiopentyl-1-phosphate -eq- H+ + 2-hydroxy 3-keto-5-methylthiopentenyl-1-phosphate. 2,3-diketo-5-methylthiopentyl-1-phosphate is also known as DK-MTP-1-P, and 2-hydroxy 3-keto-5-methylthiopentenyl-1-phosphate as HK-MTPenyl-1-P.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2-hydroxy-3-keto-5-methylthiopentenyl-1-phosphate + H2O -eq- 1,2-dihydroxy-5-(methylthio)pent-1-en-3-one + phosphate. 2-hydroxy-3-keto-5-methylthiopentenyl-1-phosphate is also known as HK-MTPenyl-P, and 1,2-dihydroxy-3-keto-5-methylthiopentene as DHK-MTPene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-2-hydroxyglutaryl-CoA -eq- H2O + glutaconyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-(hydroxymethyl)glutarate + NAD(+) -eq- 2-formylglutarate + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-octaprenyl-3-methyl-6-methoxy-1,4-benzoquinol + O2 + H+ -eq- 2-octaprenyl-3-methyl-5-hydroxy-6-methoxy-1,4-benzoquinol + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-keto-5-aminohexanoate + acetyl-CoA -eq- L-3-aminobutyryl-CoA + acetoacetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA -eq- vinylacetyl-CoA + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (4-hydroxyphenyl)acetate + H(+) -eq- 4-cresol + CO(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2,5-diamino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribitylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one + H2O -eq- 5-amino-6-(5-phospho-D-ribosylamino)uracil + ammonia.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-keto-3-deoxygalactonate -eq- D-glyceraldehyde + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-keto-3-deoxygluconate -eq- D-glyceraldehyde + pyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-amino-6-(5-phosphoribitylamino)-2,4(1H,3H)-pyrimidinedione + H2O -eq- 5-amino-6-ribitylamino-2,4(1H,3H)-pyrimidinedione + orthophosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-aminoimidazole + CO2 -eq- 5-amino-4-imidazole carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-keto-4-methylthiobutyrate + L-glutamine -eq- 2-oxoglutaramate + L-methionine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-amino-5-formylamino-6-(5-phosphoribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one + H2O -eq- 2,5-diamino-6-(5-phosphoribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one + formate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-ureido-4-imidazole carboxylate + H2O -eq- 5-amino-4-imidazole carboxylate + NH3 + CO2.
Catalysis of the oxidative decarboxylation of 6-hydroxynicotinate to 2,5-dihydroxypyridine, dependent on O2, NADH +H+ and FAD.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-hydroxynicotinate + H(2)O + O(2) -eq- 2,6-dihydroxynicotinate + H(2)O(2).

Catalysis of the reaction -  DNA containing 3-methylbase + H2O -eq- DNA with abasic site + 3-methylbase. This reaction is the hydrolysis of DNA by cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the damaged DNA 3-methylpurine or 3-methylpyrimidine base and the deoxyribose sugar to remove the methylated base, leaving an apurinic or apyrimidinic site.

Catalysis of the oxidative demethylation of N1-methyladenine and N3-methylcytosine in DNA and RNA, with concomitant decarboxylation of 2-oxoglutarate and releases oxidized methyl group on N1-methyladenine and N3-methylcytosine as formaldehyde.
Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage at apurinic or apyrimidinic sites to products with a 5'-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  methanophenazine + reduced coenzyme F420 -eq- dihydromethanophenazine + coenzyme F420.

Catalysis of the removal of uracil from a U*G mispair by the cleavage the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar. The reaction releases a free uracil and leaves an apyrimidinic (AP) site.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + 3 H(2)O -eq- 2-amino-5-formylamino-6-(1-D-ribosylamino)pyrimidin-4(3H)-one 5'-phosphate + 3 H(+) + 2 phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-2-aminoadipate + acetyl-CoA -eq- N2-acetyl-L-aminoadipate + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7,8-didemethyl-8-hydroxy-5-deazariboflavin + lactyl-2-diphospho-5'-guanosine -eq- coenzyme F420-0 + GMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + N-acetyl-L-aminoadipate -eq- ADP + N-acetyl-L-aminoadipate 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N2-acetyl-L-aminoadipyl-delta-phosphate + NADPH + H+ -eq- N2-acetyl-L-aminoadipate semialdehyde + NADP+ + orthophosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N2-acetyl-L-aminoadipate semialdehyde + L-glutamate -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + N2-acetyl-L-lysine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N2-acetyl-L-lysine + H2O -eq- acetate + L-lysine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-succinylbenzoate + H2O -eq- 2-succinyl-6-hydroxy-2,4-cyclohexadiene-1-carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phenol + MgATP + H2O -eq- phenylphosphate + MgAMP + orthophosphate.
Catalysis of the transfer of one or more alpha-D-mannose residues from GDP-mannose to positions 2,6 and others in 1-phosphatidyl-myo-inositol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (polyphosphate)n + AMP -eq- (polyphosphate)n-1 + ADP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  RTP + adenosylcobinamide -eq- adenosylcobinamide phosphate + RDP (where RTP is either ATP or GTP).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-methylpropanoyl-CoA + enzyme N6-(dihydrolipoyl)lysine -eq- CoA + enzyme N6-(S-[2-methylpropanoyl]dihydrolipoyl)lysine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-ribazole 5'-phosphate + H(2)O -eq- alpha-ribazole + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosylcobinamide + H(2)O -eq- (R)-1-aminopropan-2-ol + adenosylcobyrate.

Catalysis of the reactions -  ATP + adenosylcobyric acid + (R)-1-aminopropan-2-yl phosphate -eq- ADP + phosphate + adenosylcobinamide phosphate, and ATP + adenosylcobyric acid + (R)-1-aminopropan-2-ol -eq- ADP + phosphate + adenosylcobinamide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + acetate + CoA -eq- ADP + phosphate + acetyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + 2-methylbutanoate + CoA -eq- ADP + orthophosphate + 2-methylbutanoyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetyl-L-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- N-acetyl-2-L-amino-6-oxoheptanedioate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CDP-digeranylgeranylglycerol + L-serine -eq- archaetidylserine + CMP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + phenylacetate + CoA -eq- ADP + orthophosphate + phenylacetyl-CoA.
Modulates the activity of UTP - glucose-1-phosphate uridylyltransferase.

Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-3-O-(3-hydroxytetradecanoyl)glucosamine + (R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl-[acyl-carrier protein] -eq- UDP-2,3-bis(3-hydroxytetradecanoyl)glucosamine + [acyl-carrier protein].
